 My academic training and years of experience have prepared me to be an
 effective researcher and instructor in the Department of Mechanical and
 Aerospace Engineering.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
My research area of interest is related to the linear and nonlinear analysis
 of flat, folded, curved panels made of advanced composite materials (laminated,
 sandwich, functionally graded material, piezoelectric, variable angle tow)
 using analytical and numerical methods such as Isogeometric and finite
 element methods.
 Particularly, I deal with bending, vibration, transient, harmonic, and
 buckling analysis in both dry and hydrothermal conditions.
 During my Ph.D.
 tenure, I extensively worked on the nonlinear bending and buckling analysis
 of laminated and sandwich curved panels in hygrothermal environment under
 the supervision of Prof.
 B.
 N.
 Singh and Prof.
 D.
 K.
 Maiti.
 
\begin_inset Note Note
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
The area of research explored during my Ph.D is:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Development and implementation of 3D Elasticity solution for multilayered
 composite plates.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Navier and Levy solutions using different equivalent models for bending,
 buckling, free vibration, and transient analysis of plates/shells.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
NURBS-based isogeometric and finite element models using CLPT, FSDT, HSDT,
 and quasi-3D theories.
\begin_inset Note Note
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Comparison between different types of geometric nonlinearities, i.e., von
 Karman, Green-Lagrange, and others.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Worked on finite element model using flat, degenerated, and curved shell
 elements.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Development of mathematical models using Continuum based approach.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 I am currently working on analysis of the rotating structures under Prof.
 Donatus Oguamanam (
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "Website"
target "https://www.torontomu.ca/mechanical-industrial/people/faculty/donatus-oguamanam/"
literal "false"

\end_inset

) at TMU Canada.
 Moreover, I am also extending my Ph.D.
 works with functionally graded materials.
 Apart from this, I am also trying to do structural analysis through a deep
 learning approach.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
My future research interest is to develop various open-source modules to
 do different types of structural analysis in the field of applied mechanics.
 The benefit of doing open-source work is to make a free pathway for academician
s, researchers, and scientists so that the financial and human resources
 of our country can be utilized effectively.
 My GitHub repository contains my source codes related to my work (
